WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:04.635
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

00:20.421 --> 00:25.421
NARRATOR:
<i>Ah, the joy of Yosemite
</i> <i>and the great outdoors.</i>

00:28.295 --> 00:30.545
(WATER RUSHING)

00:33.433 --> 00:34.969
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

00:35.036 --> 00:39.407
-(DIALING)
-I'd like to order a pizza.

00:39.474 --> 00:41.976
NARRATOR: <i>It's important that
</i> <i>we put aside our busy lives</i>

00:42.043 --> 00:46.814
<i>and spend a little
</i> <i>quality time in
</i> <i>Mother Nature's house.</i>

00:46.881 --> 00:51.881
Hey! Give a bear
a little privacy, will ya?

00:53.087 --> 00:55.589
<i>That water will
</i> <i>never stop moving.</i>

00:55.656 --> 00:57.859
<i>But it's important that we do</i>

00:57.926 --> 01:01.996
<i>and reflect on the simple
</i> <i>joys of life, like camping.</i>

01:02.063 --> 01:04.499
<i>Why, here's two campers now.</i>

01:04.566 --> 01:09.566
<i>-How's it going, campers?
</i> -(PANS CLATTERING)

01:10.470 --> 01:12.720
(JERRY GIGGLES)

01:15.609 --> 01:20.048
(FLY BUZZING)

01:20.115 --> 01:23.316
<i>picking up a little
</i> <i>insect repellant will
</i> <i>make sure you don't get...</i>

01:23.383 --> 01:26.386
<i>Bugged.</i>

01:26.453 --> 01:28.553
(FLY BUZZING)

01:32.660 --> 01:37.660
<i>Advances in modern technology
</i> <i>have made tents lighter...</i>

01:37.932 --> 01:39.934
<i>More comfortable...</i>

01:40.000 --> 01:45.000
<i>And easier to
</i> <i>assemble than ever.</i>

02:08.062 --> 02:10.931
<i>You can't go camping
</i> <i>and not do a little fishing.</i>

02:10.998 --> 02:15.503
<i>Are they biting, camper?</i>

02:15.570 --> 02:19.607
<i>Sort of reminds you of
</i> <i>how life used to be
</i> <i>for our forefathers.</i>

02:19.674 --> 02:22.876
<i>If you were hungry,
</i> <i>you just went out
</i> <i>and caught your lunch.</i>

02:22.943 --> 02:25.043
(FLY BUZZING)

02:31.351 --> 02:35.055
<i>Hang in there, camper.</i>

02:35.122 --> 02:40.122
<i>You know, sometimes
</i> <i>the fish just aren't biting.</i>

02:41.061 --> 02:44.211
(BOAT MOTOR ROARING)

03:07.955 --> 03:09.905
(SPUTTERING)

03:15.696 --> 03:17.565
<i>That's the spirit, camper.</i>

03:17.632 --> 03:21.368
<i>If you don't succeed,
</i> <i>try, try and try again.</i>

03:21.435 --> 03:23.685
(LINE GROANING)

03:28.910 --> 03:33.910
<i>But at a certain point,
</i> <i>enough's enough. Right, pal?</i>

03:35.416 --> 03:39.987
<i>Ah, there's nothing better
</i> <i>than the crackling sounds
</i> <i>of a campfire.</i>

03:40.054 --> 03:43.757
<i>-But first,
</i> <i>you have to build one.
-(BLOWING)</i>

03:43.824 --> 03:48.824
<i>Looks like someone was
</i> <i>a good scout.</i>

03:49.764 --> 03:54.764
<i>Uh, starting a fire
</i> <i>so close to the tree
</i> <i>isn't the best idea.</i>

04:05.846 --> 04:08.650
(SNIFFING)

04:08.716 --> 04:11.819
<i>Everything tastes better
</i> <i>around the campfire.</i>

04:11.885 --> 04:14.454
<i>Isn't that right, camper?</i>

04:14.521 --> 04:16.021
(PANTING)

04:28.169 --> 04:32.840
<i>Even cat food, I suppose.</i>

04:32.906 --> 04:34.556
(CHOMPING)

04:58.665 --> 05:00.315
(RUMBLING)

05:04.805 --> 05:08.943
(TOM YOWLS)

05:09.010 --> 05:14.010
<i>But remember,
</i> <i>feeding wild animals is
</i> <i>never a good idea.</i>

05:14.614 --> 05:19.114
I got no problem with it. You?

05:24.558 --> 05:29.462
(STOMACH GROWLS)

05:29.529 --> 05:31.065
(BURPS)

05:31.131 --> 05:34.602
(GROWLING)

05:34.669 --> 05:37.005
NARRATOR: <i>One of
</i> <i>the best parts of camping is</i>

05:37.072 --> 05:39.908
<i>the instant rapport
</i> <i>total strangers develop.</i>

05:39.974 --> 05:43.643
<i>It's not uncommon for someone
</i> <i>to share their dinner...</i>

05:43.710 --> 05:48.210
<i>To share their dinner.</i>

05:50.584 --> 05:52.234
(SIZZLING)

05:58.359 --> 06:01.495
(SAUSAGE SQUEAKING)

06:01.562 --> 06:06.212
-(EAGLE SCREECHES)
-(SCREAMS)

06:18.712 --> 06:20.581
<i>How about that?</i>

06:20.648 --> 06:23.784
<i>Not many people get to
</i> <i>see an eagle up close.</i>

06:23.850 --> 06:28.800
<i>Isn't camping wonderful?</i>

06:33.927 --> 06:37.631
(TOM SCREAMING)

06:37.697 --> 06:38.747
(YOWLS)

07:04.892 --> 07:07.028
(VARIOUS ANIMAL SOUNDS)

07:07.095 --> 07:11.832
<i>There's nothing more relaxing
</i> <i>than mother nature singing you
</i> <i>a lullaby.</i>

07:11.899 --> 07:15.403
<i>Relaxing, isn't it?</i>

07:15.469 --> 07:18.172
(ANIMAL SOUNDS CONTINUE)

07:18.239 --> 07:21.176
-(SHUSHES)
-(SILENCE)

07:21.243 --> 07:26.243
<i>Looks like we know who
</i> <i>the king of this jungle is.</i>

07:26.748 --> 07:30.017
-(SNORING)
-(ANIMAL CALLING IN DISTANCE)

07:30.084 --> 07:34.088
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

07:34.154 --> 07:35.954
(LOW GROWL)

08:00.448 --> 08:05.448
<i>Sweet dreams, campers.
</i> <i>Tomorrow is another
</i> <i>glorious day.</i>

08:06.186 --> 08:08.886
(NARRATOR GRUNTS)

08:12.726 --> 08:16.897
(YAWNS)

08:16.964 --> 08:19.099
(SNIFFING)

08:19.166 --> 08:21.168
(CONTINUES SNIFFING)

08:21.235 --> 08:23.503
<i>Aw! Isn't that cute?
</i> <i>It's a bear!</i>

08:23.570 --> 08:25.372
(GROWLING)

08:25.439 --> 08:27.741
<i>Holy cow! It's a bear!</i>

08:27.808 --> 08:32.012
<i>Remain calm!</i>

08:32.079 --> 08:36.518
(ROARING)

08:36.585 --> 08:40.321
<i>Okay, quick!
</i> <i>Throw something in his path
</i> <i>to distract him!</i>

08:40.387 --> 08:43.290
<i>That'll work!</i>

08:43.357 --> 08:44.857
(ROARING)

09:08.982 --> 09:12.752
(ROARING)

09:12.819 --> 09:15.088
Phew!

09:15.155 --> 09:16.655
(ROARING)

09:28.435 --> 09:29.935
(ROARING)

09:55.095 --> 10:00.045
(VISITORS TALKING
INDISTINCTLY)

10:03.505 --> 10:08.505
NARRATOR: <i>So we end
</i> <i>our story on the breath-taking
</i> <i>beauty of Half Dome...</i>

10:09.276 --> 10:11.211
<i>An American treasure.</i>

10:11.278 --> 10:16.278
<i>A landmark that will
</i> <i>endure forever.</i>

10:23.757 --> 10:25.857
(FLY BUZZING)

10:32.032 --> 10:37.005
(ROARING)

10:37.071 --> 10:39.673
<i>Hope you enjoyed
</i> <i>your camping trip.</i>

10:39.739 --> 10:40.841
<i>Hurry back now.</i>
